   - This part uses the sine function to introduce periodicity into the priority calculation. It scales the sine function by the difference between the item size and each bin size, which helps in capturing the cyclical nature of the bin packing problem.

The combination of these two components ensures that the priority score reflects both the exponential decay and the periodic nature of the bin sizes relative to the item size. Each implementation is unique in the sense that the order of operations or the specific functions used may vary slightly, but the overall approach remains consistent.

